KW  - Trigger strategies
KW  - Policy games
AB  - I consider an example of a two-country model featuring national heterogeneity, and demonstrate that heterogeneity plays an important role for the countries' gains from international policy cooperation, and - just as important - for the incentives to break the cooperative agreement. I find that national heterogeneity unambiguously reduces trigger strategies' support for policy cooperation. In other words, the more countries differ, the harder it is to sustain policy cooperation.
